P.S. 171Q believes our school community is a true family, and we work to establish strong connections amongst students, staff and families so that all feel welcome and supported each day. We believe arts are vital to student success and students in every grade get to participate in a form of art whether it is dance, music, or visual arts. We, at PS171, develop a well rounded child preparing them for success in their future! The Autism Horizon Program supports students with autism in a special class with eight students, a special education teacher and paraprofessional with emphasis on building skills and offering opportunities for meaningful inclusion in larger settings. Students in this program may need additional academic support and require speech and language services, including in areas of social or pragmatic communication. results.overview:
PS 177 is an amazing community school of learners and high academic expectations. We pride ourselves on building student leaders that are celebrated every month and selected based on criteria grounded in 4 values of success and leadership. 
Our student and staff exemplify pride, achievement, cooperation and kindness - making PS 177 A Pack Above the Rest. Honor roll students make up 40% of the student population. All students have access to enrichment afterschool programs and STEM, arts, and YALE RULER throughout the day. We offer support for our ELL students throughout the day as well as an afterschool program. 
Our families participate in free English language classes twice a week for the entire year. We also offer an enrichment program to students that excel in academics (our iXL Champions). 
Our teachers are all trained in the Science of Reading and receive direct support throughout the year to enhance their pedagogical practices. 
Every grade participates in health and wellness cooking classes each year as well as a multitude of physical activities (gym, move to improve, soccer, and amazing athletes). 
In addition to the above we also offer 1:1 morning tutoring for students that demonstrate a need. We offer families a two hour extended day after school hosted by the FIAO. 
PS 177 supports all of its families, students and of course staff in all ways.
